8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 8, L.D. 44, “An Act to Amend the Laws
10 Pertaining to Elver Fishing”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of the emergency preamble.
12 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1.
13 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 3 and inserting the following:
14 'Sec. 3. 12 MRSA §6505-A, sub-§2, ¶F, as amended by PL 2017, c. 250, §4, is
15 further amended to read:
16 F. Becomes eligible to obtain an elver fishing license pursuant to the elver lottery
17 under subsection 2‑C and who has completed any educational requirements established
18 under section 6505-E.'
19 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 5 and inserting the following:
20 'Sec. 5. 12 MRSA §6505-A, sub-§3-A, as amended by PL 2015, c. 131, §1, and
21 PL 2023, c. 369, Pt. A, §4 and affected by §5, is further amended to read:
22 3-A. Elver fishing quotas. The commissioner may adopt rules to establish, implement
23 and administer an elver individual fishing quota system in order to ensure that the elver
24 fishery annual landings do not exceed the overall annual quota established by the Atlantic
25 States Marine Fisheries Commission. Prior to allocating any portion of the overall annual
26 quota for the State established pursuant to paragraph A, the commissioner may withhold
27 up to 1% of the available overall annual quota. Except as provided in section 6575‑L, a
28 person issued a license under this section or section 6302‑A, subsection 3, paragraph E,
29 E‑1, F or G may not take, possess or sell elvers in excess of the weight quota allocated to
30 that person under the quota system. The rules must:
31 A. Establish an overall annual quota for the State;
32 B. Establish the amount of the overall annual quota under paragraph A that is allocated
33 to persons licensed under this section and specify a formula to establish individual
34 quotas for persons licensed under this section. The formula may take into account the
