315 amount of elvers a person licensed under this section lawfully harvested in previous
326 seasons based on final harvesting reports. The rules must specify the date by which
337 harvester reports are considered final for the purpose of determining individual quotas;
348 and
5 C. Provide, in accordance with section 6302‑B, that 21.9% of the overall annual quota
6 under paragraph A is allocated to the federally recognized Indian tribes in the State and
7 establish the amount of that portion of the overall annual quota allocated to the
8 Passamaquoddy Tribe, the Penobscot Nation, the Houlton Band of Maliseet Indians
9 and the Mi'kmaq Nation.
10 If persons issued licenses under this section collectively exceed the overall annual quota
11 allocated to those persons pursuant to paragraph B, the number of pounds by which the
12 license holders exceeded that overall annual quota must be deducted from the following
13 year’s overall annual quota allocated to persons licensed under this section. If the overage
14 exceeds the overall annual quota allocated to persons licensed under this section for the
15 following year, the overage must be deducted from the overall annual quota allocated to
16 persons licensed under this section in subsequent years until the entire overage has been
17 accounted for.
18 The commissioner may adopt or amend rules on an emergency basis if immediate action is
19 necessary to establish and implement the elver individual fishing quota in advance of the
20 beginning of the elver fishing season.
21 Rules adopted pursuant to this subsection are routine technical rules as defined in Title 5,
22 chapter 375, subchapter 2‑A.
23 Sec. 6. 12 MRSA §6505-E is enacted to read:
24 §6505-E. Elver handling training course
25 Prior to the issuance of an elver fishing license, the commissioner may require an
26 applicant to complete an educational course that the commissioner determines appropriate
27 to provide necessary information regarding the proper handling of elvers to ensure
28 survivability.'
29 Amend the bill by striking out all of the emergency clause.
30 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
31 number to read consecutively.
32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment removes the emergency preamble and emergency clause from the bill.
3344 The amendment allows the Commissioner of Marine Resources to require certain
3355 applicants for an elver fishing license to complete an educational course and gives the
3366 commissioner the authority to withhold up to 1% of the available overall annual elver quota
3377 for the State before allocating any portion of the overall annual quota. The amendment also
3388 removes limits on possession of elvers established by the bill and removes the changes
3399 regarding the suspension of a license or certificate made by the bill.
40 The amendment also removes from the bill the provision permitting an elver fishing
41 license holder to whom a fyke net tag is issued to allow another license holder to empty the
42 fyke net of the tag holder under the tag holder's supervision.
